The paper deals with analyzing voting mechanisms, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of LP-duality and flow interpretations suggests a connection to optimization and graph theory (cs.DS), while the analysis of social choice rules using worst-case distortion ratios is a common approach in algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the distortion bounds of specific voting rules, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
